<h4 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h4>
<p>Be careful that you do not try to take the logarithm of a negative number. A common practice is to write <span class="process-math">\(\int\inverse
x\dx{x}=\ln(x)+C\text{,}\)</span> even though this is only valid for .  We will adopt this practice, and resort to an absolute value only when there is an issue about being negative.</p>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-2.html#p-20" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
